To chime in on the hot wings thing, people should really use a scoville rating and try and make it mainstream. I've had some food described as hot that, in reality, was mild as a friggin' bell pepper. Okay obviously "HOT" wings is a tip-off but tbh

people who ask that are probably just wondering if there is actually any kick to it or not. If someone asked me I'd probably just say "oh its just a cayenne powder coating" or "yeah it was marinaded in habanero sauce" or something
A good comparison would be a jalapeno pepper
The range is much wider, but they tend to be in the 3,000 - 5,000 scovilles range
Your standard "hot" hot sauce will land towards the lower end
